<topic id="translation-package-builder-addon">
  <title>DITA Translation Package Builder Add-on</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Add-ons<indexterm>Translation package builder</indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm>Translation package builder add-on</indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p id="p_owg_dgk_54b"><ph keyref="product"/> offers an add-on that contributes contextual menu actions that help
      you build a translation package for DITA files that can be sent to translators. You can also
      extract the changed files back into your project once you receive the package back from the
      translators.</p>
    <section id="section_tdq_wvx_qsb">
      <title>Quick Installation</title>
      <p conkeyref="reusables-addons/p_install_button" id="p_hzl_4xg_rsb"/>
      <p id="p_x42_bwx_qsb"><foreign outputclass="html-embed"><![CDATA[
               <a
          title = "Drag and drop in the Oxygen editing area to install (Oxygen 24.1 and newer)."
          href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/InstData/Addons/default/updateSite.xml?oxygenAddonId=com.oxygenxml.translation.support.TranslationPackageBuilderPlugin"
          style="padding: 8px; border: 1px solid #cbcbcb; border-radius: 4px; cursor: grab;color:black;
          text-decoration:none;"><img style="vertical-align:middle;" src=" data:image/png;base64,"/><span>Install</span></a>]]></foreign></p>
    </section>
    <section id="section_zmt_bzg_rsb">
      <title>Manual Installation</title>
      <p id="p_pwg_dgk_54b">To manually install it the add-on, follow these instructions:<ol
          id="ol_qwg_dgk_54b">
          <li id="li_rwg_dgk_54b">Go to <menucascade>
              <uicontrol>Help</uicontrol>
              <uicontrol>Install new add-ons</uicontrol>
            </menucascade> to open an add-on selection dialog box.</li>
          <li id="li_swg_dgk_54b">Enter or paste
              <b>https://www.oxygenxml.com/InstData/Addons/default/updateSite.xml</b> in the
              <uicontrol>Show add-ons from</uicontrol> field or select it from the drop-down
            menu.</li>
          <li id="li_twg_dgk_54b">Select the <b>DITA Translation Package Builder</b> add-on and
            click <uicontrol>Next</uicontrol>.</li>
          <li id="li_uwg_dgk_54b">Read the end-user license agreement. Then select the <uicontrol>I
              accept all terms of the end-user license agreement</uicontrol> option and click
              <uicontrol>Finish</uicontrol>.</li>
          <li id="li_vwg_dgk_54b">Restart the application.</li>
        </ol></p>
      <p id="p_wwg_dgk_54b"><b>Result:</b> A <uicontrol>Translation Package Builder</uicontrol>
        submenu will now be available in the contextual menu of the <uicontrol>DITA Maps
          Manager</uicontrol>. This submenu includes actions to generate a ZIP package of modified
        files that can be sent to translators, as well as an action to extract translated files back
        into your DITA project.</p>
    </section>
    <p id="p_xwg_dgk_54b">For more information, see the <xref
        href="https://github.com/oxygenxml/Translation-Package-Builder" format="html"
        scope="external">details for this <b>Translation Package Builder</b> add-on in
      GitHub</xref>.</p>
    <section id="section_x2n_vhh_vrb">
      <title>Resources</title>
      <p id="p_orm_dgk_54b">For more information about the Translation Package Builder add-on, as
        well as details regarding other popular add-ons that extend the functionality of <ph
          keyref="product"/>, watch the following webinars/presentation:<ul id="ul_kgv_tx1_jsb">
          <li id="li_lgv_tx1_jsb"><xref
              href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/events/2021/webinar_add_ons_you_can_use_for_technical_writing.html"
              format="html" scope="external">Webinar: Add-ons You Can Use for Technical
              Writing</xref></li>
          <li><xref
              href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/events/2020/webinar_automate_xml_processing_with_oxygen_xml_scripting.html"
              format="html" scope="external">Webinar: Automate XML processing with Oxygen XML
              Scripting</xref></li>
        </ul></p>
    </section>
  </body>
